1
00:00:09,620 --> 00:00:11,620
Wait up, King!

2
00:00:13,460 --> 00:00:15,620
You’re slow, Tabo!

3
00:00:18,260 --> 00:00:20,660
Attack with Blue-Eyes!

4
00:00:20,660 --> 00:00:23,680
Or so you'd think...
Mirror Force activated!

5
00:00:23,680 --> 00:00:25,120
Damn it!

6
00:00:26,120 --> 00:00:27,800
Are you a kid or what?

7
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:30,620
- We’re done!
- Enough already.

8
00:00:34,920 --> 00:00:39,620
I’m serious, we’re done!
You get that?

9
00:00:39,620 --> 00:00:42,120
We’re done!

10
00:00:51,620 --> 00:01:00,620
Last night, in Yokohama's Naka Ward, Emi Nakajima,
34, was hit by a large truck in an accident.

11
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:10,120
Ms. Nakajima suddenly ran onto the road
in the rain and was likely hit by the truck.

12
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:13,360
The paramedics responded to the call…

13
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:15,120
- Excuse me.
- Hello!

14
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:16,620
Hello!

15
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:51,280
THE RIGHT TO JUDJE

16
00:03:44,860 --> 00:03:49,620
It looks like the police are
calling this case an accident for now.

17
00:03:51,260 --> 00:03:54,120
What are the odds of that?

18
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:56,960
We’ll just have to
handle this ourselves.

19
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:06,240
- Koyama's in Japan?
- Yeah.

20
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:10,620
He’s having a press conference
and knew about the incident.

21
00:04:10,620 --> 00:04:13,360
He didn’t really believe it though.

22
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:15,120
Coincidence?

23
00:04:16,620 --> 00:04:18,280
What is?

24
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:20,620
Nothing.

25
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:26,120
The next target is probably Tabo.

26
00:04:27,740 --> 00:04:31,620
So, how do you know that?

27
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:35,620
It’s just...

28
00:04:35,620 --> 00:04:37,620
Please tell me properly.

29
00:04:47,260 --> 00:04:53,340
Tabo made a song that includes
the names of the six of us.

30
00:04:53,340 --> 00:04:54,460
One, two…

31
00:04:54,460 --> 00:04:56,800
- One day Hin…
- Yes!

32
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:59,080
- In the forest Kantaro…
- Yes.

33
00:04:59,080 --> 00:05:01,140
- A bear and Nico…
- Yes!

34
00:05:01,140 --> 00:05:04,420
- Met Tabo…
- Yes!

35
00:05:04,420 --> 00:05:08,560
So far, they’ve been targeted
in that exact order.

36
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:10,560
Why made a song like that?

37
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:14,040
Like a symbol of friendship?

38
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:19,020
A symbol of friendship?
You’d forgotten all about that.

39
00:05:19,020 --> 00:05:21,120
It doesn’t matter.

40
00:05:22,260 --> 00:05:26,120
Anyway, Tabo is probably the next target.

41
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:35,620
He remembered a song you’d forgotten
and just happened to come back to Japan...

42
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:41,120
What’re you trying to say?

43
00:05:44,860 --> 00:05:49,340
Tabo’s being targeted too, right?
He’s not the one, obviously.

44
00:05:49,340 --> 00:05:51,840
Or maybe you just want to believe that?

45
00:05:54,620 --> 00:05:59,120
Either way, keep close contact with him.

46
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,300
Huh?

47
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:02,200
You were best friends, right?

48
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:06,780
I’ll approach in my own way.

49
00:06:06,780 --> 00:06:11,620
But there might be things
only best friends can talk about.

50
00:06:17,380 --> 00:06:19,620
I said it.

51
00:06:19,620 --> 00:06:23,620
- I said it, I did.
- Yes.

52
00:06:23,620 --> 00:06:36,380
Next news: A man's body was found
in Tokyo Bay; police are investigating the case.

53
00:06:36,380 --> 00:06:37,620
Dad?

54
00:06:37,620 --> 00:06:47,120
At 6:30 a.m., a man reported to police
seeing a person-like figure floating in the sea.

55
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:52,400
When police officers rushed to the scene,
near the breakwater they found an adult male...

56
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:56,120
- Dad.
- Huh? Sorry, what?

57
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:58,620
- It’s nothing.
- Yes.

58
00:06:58,620 --> 00:07:01,360
Kanon, make sure you eat
the mushrooms too.

59
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:04,120
- Okay.
- Alright, let’s eat.

60
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:06,620
Nothing to identify from the
belongings either...

61
00:07:06,620 --> 00:07:08,120
Turning off the TV.

62
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:11,960
- Let’s eat.
- Let’s eat.

63
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:13,360
Let’s eat.

64
00:07:13,860 --> 00:07:17,120
Switching to the new
release announcement.

65
00:07:19,420 --> 00:07:20,800
CEO?

66
00:07:22,300 --> 00:07:24,320
How is it?

67
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:28,120
Yeah... got it.
You can proceed with that.

68
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:30,120
Understood.
We'll take care of it.

69
00:07:34,820 --> 00:07:36,820
- Excuse me.
- Yes.

70
00:07:59,620 --> 00:08:01,780
Sato this and Kato that...

71
00:08:01,780 --> 00:08:04,400
- We'll follow up on Kato.
- Got it.

72
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:06,120
Ah...

73
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:10,780
- Let me follow him.
- What’s next?

74
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:14,620
Takahiro Koyama, huh...

75
00:08:15,660 --> 00:08:18,060
I hear he’s pretty capable.

76
00:08:18,060 --> 00:08:21,440
He’s got nerves of steel.

77
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:23,660
All alone in the U.S., huh...

78
00:08:23,660 --> 00:08:25,340
But why?

79
00:08:25,340 --> 00:08:29,660
A revolutionary in the app industry,
but surrounded by dark rumors.

80
00:08:29,660 --> 00:08:31,160
A revolutionary, huh...

81
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:35,160
He’ll do whatever it takes.
Even if it’s against the law.

82
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:39,020
There are plenty of guys like that.
Why Koyama?

83
00:08:39,020 --> 00:08:43,420
Or rather, do you even need
to be the one doing this?

84
00:08:43,420 --> 00:08:45,660
We were classmates
in elementary school.

85
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:49,160
Hmm.

86
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:51,160
Please.

87
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:02,660
Sorry to keep you waiting.
Here's your iced coffee.

88
00:09:04,580 --> 00:09:06,160
Thank you.

89
00:09:09,160 --> 00:09:11,340
Yeah, this is good!

90
00:09:11,340 --> 00:09:14,440
Japanese steak is the best!

91
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:17,680
Man, we’ve really grown up.

92
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:20,780
I could never imagine
eating steak every day.

93
00:09:20,780 --> 00:09:22,060
Yeah...

94
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:27,080
- King, eat up.
- Oh, yeah, I will.

95
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:30,440
Sorry for making you come all the way.

96
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:33,160
The next presentation’s right there.

97
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:36,680
They wouldn’t let me off work at all.

98
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:39,800
Let’s go eat some
fancy Chinese food next time.

99
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:47,660
We used to fight over leftover fried bread
and frozen mandarins, huh.

100
00:09:47,660 --> 00:09:49,660
Yeah, we did.

101
00:09:49,660 --> 00:09:54,640
Everyone was hyping me up,
so I went for it even though I wasn’t hungry.

102
00:09:54,640 --> 00:09:57,780
- I get it.
- What, King, you too?

103
00:09:57,780 --> 00:10:00,820
- Yeah.
- Really?

104
00:10:00,820 --> 00:10:02,580
Those were good times.

105
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:04,660
- Sorry to keep you waiting.
- Yeah...

106
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:18,740
I can’t believe there’s
a killer among those guys.

107
00:10:18,740 --> 00:10:20,160
Huh?

108
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:23,000
King, you feel the same, right?

109
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:27,000
No... well, that’s...

110
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,500
Who’s been pushing you into this?

111
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:33,000
You can’t investigate that much alone, right?

112
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,660
Well...

113
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,160
Sonoko Saruhashi.

114
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:44,360
Those six used to bully Sonoko Saruhashi...

115
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:46,160
Aka “Donoko.”

116
00:10:50,140 --> 00:10:52,020
You remember that?

117
00:10:52,940 --> 00:10:55,160
I remember it clearly.

118
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:59,640
No wonder she holds a grudge.

119
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:05,660
But she can’t just say "I'll kill you" and expect
compliance. We must stop it ourselves.

120
00:11:05,660 --> 00:11:07,360
That’s not it.

121
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:08,960
Huh?

122
00:11:10,060 --> 00:11:12,280
It’s not her.

123
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:14,160
What are you talking about?

124
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:21,040
Well… when Kantaro was attacked,
she was with me.

125
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:23,440
So it’s impossible.

126
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:26,820
- And right now, she’s...
- So it really is her, huh.

127
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:31,160
She’s a famous reporter now, right?

128
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:39,860
- You’re too easily fooled.
- I’m serious, it’s really not her.

129
00:11:39,860 --> 00:11:43,800
She’s taking revenge on us
for what we did.

130
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:46,160
How can you not get
something so simple?

131
00:11:49,660 --> 00:11:54,160
She wouldn't do something like that.

132
00:11:59,020 --> 00:12:08,840
I can't explain it well, but Sonoko Saruhashi has been
struggling desperately to change herself.

133
00:12:09,980 --> 00:12:14,020
So I don't think she’d seek revenge.

134
00:12:15,180 --> 00:12:19,660
You trust her but doubt the rest of us?

135
00:12:23,520 --> 00:12:25,900
You're way too simple-minded.

136
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:29,840
I don't know what she told you,
but you're a target too.

137
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:33,140
Fine, if you want to get
along with her, suit yourself.

138
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:39,160
Tabo.

139
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:43,660
Be careful.

140
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:07,400
Ultimately, they ruled it an accident.

141
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:09,660
I wonder what they’re thinking.

142
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:15,160
Probably nothing, right?

143
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:24,160
Sorry, I get that a lot too.

144
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:30,080
So, how’s Koyama been?

145
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:33,660
He returned to Japan about a week ago.

146
00:13:33,660 --> 00:13:37,660
He just goes back and forth
between his company and the hotel.

147
00:13:37,660 --> 00:13:39,500
Almost unnaturally so.

148
00:13:44,660 --> 00:13:46,660
They were all classmates.

149
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:50,860
Next is the motive…

150
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:57,160
Back in elementary school... huh.

151
00:14:03,660 --> 00:14:07,660
Damn it, hey, hey, hey.

152
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:12,880
You’re acting way too confident!

153
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:15,660
Playing against you is a breeze, Ucchan.

154
00:14:15,660 --> 00:14:18,280
There’s no way I’m losing…!

155
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:20,540
Ah... wait, wait...
Hey, hey, hey...!

156
00:14:21,940 --> 00:14:24,160
Don’t you look a bit down?

157
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,400
Yeah...

158
00:14:26,520 --> 00:14:29,940
So I saw my best friend
from elementary school.

159
00:14:29,940 --> 00:14:31,660
That’s exciting!

160
00:14:31,660 --> 00:14:34,060
So? Did you have a fight?

161
00:14:34,060 --> 00:14:35,160
No, but…

162
00:14:37,380 --> 00:14:39,340
That’s a downer.

163
00:14:40,420 --> 00:14:43,320
Grown adults don’t need to fight…

164
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:45,660
Fool, looking away like that.

165
00:14:45,660 --> 00:14:47,160
Take this!

166
00:14:58,140 --> 00:15:03,660
- So yeah, I cut him off.
- Cut him off? As adults?

167
00:15:03,660 --> 00:15:06,540
No, not now,
back in elementary school.

168
00:15:07,260 --> 00:15:08,660
Right here.

169
00:15:08,660 --> 00:15:10,660
- Wa... water...
- Yeah, water...

170
00:15:10,660 --> 00:15:13,520
- Water, gold, earth, fire, wood...
- Yes.

171
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:15,920
Mars lies next to Earth.

172
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:19,360
At its closest,
it’s about 50 million kilometers away.

173
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:21,160
Oh!

174
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:29,020
His name’s Tabo.
He was smart and rich...

175
00:15:29,020 --> 00:15:30,660
Here I go.

176
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:39,440
He was good at sports and popular.

177
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:40,660
Bang!
Bang!

178
00:15:40,660 --> 00:15:42,620
Yeah!

179
00:15:42,620 --> 00:15:45,160
- Finally got all three cards.
- Yeah.

180
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:47,980
This is proof of our friendship.

181
00:15:47,980 --> 00:15:50,660
- Yeah.
- A treasure for life, okay?

182
00:15:50,660 --> 00:15:55,720
I played with him every day,
he was my best friend.

183
00:15:57,140 --> 00:15:58,780
Best friend, huh...

184
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:02,360
That’s nice.

185
00:16:05,700 --> 00:16:09,440
Why did you cut ties with a
best friend like that?

186
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:11,160
Yeah...

187
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,980
Tabo, let’s go to the arcade today.

188
00:16:15,980 --> 00:16:17,240
No...

189
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:20,440
Then let’s go to Minami Park.

190
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:22,980
It’s not that...

191
00:16:22,980 --> 00:16:24,660
What’s wrong?

192
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:29,500
I have tutoring school today.

193
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:33,220
- Tabo, let’s go.
- Yeah.

194
00:16:33,220 --> 00:16:37,220
As graduation neared,
everyone went to tutoring school.

195
00:16:37,220 --> 00:16:41,680
Since I didn’t take the exams,
I felt kind of lonely…

196
00:16:41,680 --> 00:16:48,600
And, you know… growing up
just didn’t feel that exciting.

197
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:50,660
And then, at a time like that...

198
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:55,520
- You did well on the test.
- Thanks.

199
00:16:55,520 --> 00:16:58,840
- Tabo.
- Yeah?

200
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:04,660
Kantaro had his "Winged Dragon of Ra"
taken by North Junior High guys.

201
00:17:04,660 --> 00:17:07,660
- Yeah...
- Really sorry about that.

202
00:17:07,660 --> 00:17:10,560
Let’s go get it back together.

203
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:12,660
You’re coming, right?

204
00:17:12,660 --> 00:17:15,660
Well... Me? I’ll pass.

205
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:19,480
What do you mean?

206
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:23,780
Well, I think I lost my Obelisk too.

207
00:17:23,780 --> 00:17:25,160
Huh?

208
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:34,040
Whatever, we don’t really
need that stuff.

209
00:17:35,540 --> 00:17:37,160
Nothing will change.

210
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:41,660
That’s something really important!

211
00:17:41,660 --> 00:17:43,160
Let go.

212
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:48,160
There are more important things!

213
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:55,800
Is tutoring school that important to you?!

214
00:17:55,800 --> 00:18:00,080
So if we go to different schools,
that’s it for us?!

215
00:18:00,080 --> 00:18:03,160
I never said that!
Are you a kid or what!

216
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:05,160
Who’s the kid here,
you damn geek!

217
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:07,160
You’re the one, you damn kid!

218
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:10,660
Both of you, stop it already!
King!

219
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:16,660
- We’re done!
- Enough already.

220
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:23,660
I’m serious, we’re done!
You get that?

221
00:18:23,660 --> 00:18:26,660
That’s how we kind of
ended up cutting ties...

222
00:18:28,160 --> 00:18:31,660
Huh?
You’re still holding onto that?

223
00:18:31,660 --> 00:18:34,680
I’m not sure if he remember,

224
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:43,600
but I just can’t really talk to him well.
It’s like… I can’t pretend it never happened.

225
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:47,000
Then why not just make up?

226
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:51,560
Listen, Moeka,
adults don’t make up that easily.

227
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:54,260
Huh? Adults are such a drag.

228
00:18:54,260 --> 00:18:56,840
Yeah, it’s such a drag.

229
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:58,660
- Can I get another one?
- Okay.

230
00:19:00,240 --> 00:19:04,440
The press conference will be held
as scheduled at 5 p.m. tomorrow.

231
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:05,620
Got it.

232
00:19:05,620 --> 00:19:09,760
Also, there’s an interview request...

233
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:11,420
- An interview?
- Yes.

234
00:19:11,420 --> 00:19:14,220
Tell them I don’t do
individual interviews.

235
00:19:17,660 --> 00:19:19,660
He has just arrived.

236
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:28,420
Thank you for waiting.

237
00:19:28,420 --> 00:19:32,540
No, thank you for taking
time out of your busy schedule.

238
00:19:32,540 --> 00:19:36,540
It’s an honor to be interviewed
by Sonoko Saruhashi.

239
00:19:38,040 --> 00:19:40,040
Likewise.

240
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:50,560
It looks really nice now.

241
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:52,540
Is this all right?

242
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:56,040
- Good work.
- Yeah.

243
00:19:56,040 --> 00:19:57,880
That’s plenty.

244
00:19:57,880 --> 00:20:02,840
It doesn’t change what happened,
but my feelings have really changed.

245
00:20:02,840 --> 00:20:06,340
- Thank you.
- That’s good to hear.

246
00:20:06,340 --> 00:20:09,540
- Alright then, take care.
- Yes, thank you.

247
00:20:11,660 --> 00:20:13,600
Is that enough?

248
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:15,940
Yes, I also have ramen.

249
00:20:27,540 --> 00:20:31,540
- Hello.
- Yes, this is Takaki.

250
00:20:31,540 --> 00:20:35,040
Sorry for the sudden call.
This is Kaneda from the MPD.

251
00:20:36,540 --> 00:20:40,040
Actually, Mr. Sakurai just...

252
00:20:44,040 --> 00:20:47,040
What was the purpose of
your return to Japan this time?

253
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:51,900
Tonight, there’s a reception to
unveil our company’s new service.

254
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:53,540
That’s the reason.

255
00:20:53,540 --> 00:20:58,040
I believe your company
also received an invitation.

256
00:20:58,040 --> 00:21:02,040
It was supposed to be held by the
new business division, right?

257
00:21:02,040 --> 00:21:04,540
So why is CEO coming in person?

258
00:21:04,540 --> 00:21:08,540
I really wanted to announce it myself.

259
00:21:08,540 --> 00:21:11,300
Really?

260
00:21:11,300 --> 00:21:14,700
I heard the employees were confused.

261
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:16,820
It was supposed to be a surprise...

262
00:21:16,820 --> 00:21:22,040
It’s a new service that uses VR technology to
provide a realistic visual experience.

263
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:26,260
With this, you can travel anywhere
while staying at home.

264
00:21:26,260 --> 00:21:30,540
Even overseas, and even to space, actually.

265
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:34,040
Space...

266
00:21:35,540 --> 00:21:37,040
Yes.

267
00:21:39,740 --> 00:21:43,340
I heard rumors about
downsizing the design department.

268
00:21:43,340 --> 00:21:47,760
There’s even talk of lawsuits
due to aggressive layoffs.

269
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:53,700
With that going on, where is the budget
for the new business coming from?

270
00:21:53,700 --> 00:21:56,540
What exactly are you trying to say?

271
00:21:56,540 --> 00:22:06,040
Many said Takahiro Koyama never hesitates
to use any means in your company.

272
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:10,540
That’s you, right, Donoko?

273
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:22,880
Mr. Takaki.

274
00:22:23,980 --> 00:22:26,980
Ah... how’s Kantaro?

275
00:22:39,480 --> 00:22:41,480
Kantaro...

276
00:22:48,980 --> 00:22:51,480
Thank goodness...

277
00:22:52,980 --> 00:22:59,520
Sorry for making you worry...

278
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,480
Excuse me.

279
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:12,820
The police questioned me nonstop…

280
00:23:12,820 --> 00:23:14,980
It’s so frustrating...

281
00:23:14,980 --> 00:23:16,980
What happened?

282
00:23:18,120 --> 00:23:23,980
While I was preparing...
It seems I fell asleep...

283
00:23:25,980 --> 00:23:28,760
Maybe I was just tired...

284
00:23:28,760 --> 00:23:31,480
What are you doing?

285
00:23:35,240 --> 00:23:37,480
I’m sorry...

286
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:41,980
No... I’m really glad you’re alive.

287
00:23:56,980 --> 00:24:01,480
That... was from Tabo...

288
00:24:05,980 --> 00:24:09,980
Right after Hin passed away...

289
00:24:12,260 --> 00:24:15,980
I got a call from Tabo...

290
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:19,660
From Tabo?

291
00:24:19,660 --> 00:24:21,480
Yeah...

292
00:24:22,780 --> 00:24:25,480
About the reunion...

293
00:24:28,980 --> 00:24:35,980
We talked about a lot of things...
he said he’d be coming back to Japan right away.

294
00:24:41,340 --> 00:24:47,980
But... I ended up like this...

295
00:24:50,620 --> 00:24:57,980
He must’ve heard about it on the news
and came to visit me.

296
00:25:02,980 --> 00:25:05,820
What did Tabo say on the phone?

297
00:25:05,820 --> 00:25:07,980
This part’s off the record.

298
00:25:13,980 --> 00:25:18,480
The other day, I got this photo
sent from an anonymous email address.

299
00:25:21,980 --> 00:25:28,980
I investigated it too,
and it’s a photo only the culprit could have taken.

300
00:25:28,980 --> 00:25:34,480
They probably thought I’d panic
and rush over after seeing this.

301
00:25:36,480 --> 00:25:41,480
Because if I come back to Japan,
they can kill me.

302
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:43,480
Am I wrong?

303
00:25:54,380 --> 00:25:59,240
You and that person,
you’re both really idiots.

304
00:25:59,240 --> 00:26:01,640
Nothing’s changed.

305
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:03,480
Huh?

306
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:06,680
Do you know how I felt?

307
00:26:06,680 --> 00:26:10,020
- Who’s inside there?
- Stop it!

308
00:26:10,020 --> 00:26:13,260
Who’s inside there?

309
00:26:13,260 --> 00:26:15,600
Who’s inside there?

310
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:17,480
Help me!

311
00:26:19,980 --> 00:26:24,980
Even after 20 years,
I still resent you.

312
00:26:26,760 --> 00:26:28,420
So, after all...

313
00:26:28,420 --> 00:26:32,480
But I would never kill or let you die.

314
00:26:33,780 --> 00:26:35,360
Why?

315
00:26:37,380 --> 00:26:40,980
Because I’m different from you guys.

316
00:26:40,980 --> 00:26:48,980
I'm different from bad kids
who mock others' misfortune or pain.

317
00:27:03,980 --> 00:27:09,980
Because I’m different from you who
will never change and can’t change.

318
00:27:14,060 --> 00:27:16,480
King’s right.

319
00:27:17,840 --> 00:27:22,480
Tabo said he got a message from you.

320
00:27:24,980 --> 00:27:29,480
He only came to pick up the painting.

321
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:37,980
He was worried about you, King...

322
00:27:37,980 --> 00:27:43,900
And told me to watch over you
so you don’t do anything reckless.

323
00:27:43,900 --> 00:27:45,980
He said he’ll be back soon...

324
00:27:47,480 --> 00:27:50,480
So don’t let you do
anything unnecessary.

325
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:55,480
What’s that supposed to mean?

326
00:27:57,980 --> 00:28:00,980
Then he should’ve told me directly.

327
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:04,980
I said that too.

328
00:28:06,760 --> 00:28:08,080
But...

329
00:28:11,860 --> 00:28:13,540
Tabo...

330
00:28:15,980 --> 00:28:21,480
He said he cut ties with you, but…

331
00:28:24,480 --> 00:28:29,480
He’s always regretted it...

332
00:28:32,980 --> 00:28:35,480
Cutting ties with you…

333
00:28:36,980 --> 00:28:39,480
And never apologized...

334
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:43,680
Is tutoring school that important to you?!

335
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:47,780
So if we go to different schools,
that’s it for us?!

336
00:28:47,780 --> 00:28:51,280
I never said that!
Are you a kid or what!

337
00:28:51,280 --> 00:28:53,180
Who’s the kid here,
you damn geek!

338
00:28:53,180 --> 00:28:55,300
You’re the one, you damn kid!

339
00:28:55,300 --> 00:28:58,480
Both of you, stop it already!
King!

340
00:28:58,480 --> 00:29:01,480
- We’re done!
- Enough already.

341
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:07,980
I’m serious, we’re done!
You get that?

342
00:29:17,480 --> 00:29:19,980
King, are you okay?

343
00:29:19,980 --> 00:29:22,980
Yeah, it’s nothing serious.

344
00:29:22,980 --> 00:29:24,980
What about the cards?

345
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:30,480
Tabo, you know...

346
00:29:31,980 --> 00:29:40,480
He actually didn’t want
to take the entrance exams...

347
00:29:40,480 --> 00:29:47,480
He wanted to go to the
same middle school as you…

348
00:29:48,860 --> 00:29:51,480
He kept saying that...

349
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:58,480
Then why did he?

350
00:30:00,140 --> 00:30:04,540
- Because it was a promise...
- A promise?

351
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:07,980
Sorry for doubting you.

352
00:30:11,160 --> 00:30:13,980
But stop dragging King into this.

353
00:30:13,980 --> 00:30:19,320
He’s an idiot. Keeps moving without care,
even though he’s the target.

354
00:30:19,320 --> 00:30:22,480
If it’s about the case, I’ll cooperate.

355
00:30:22,480 --> 00:30:25,620
No... I want to help.

356
00:30:27,460 --> 00:30:31,860
You’re a target too, you know?
You understand that, right?

357
00:30:31,860 --> 00:30:34,480
Everyone’s being killed
as shown in the painting.

358
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:37,880
If the culprit knew about
that press conference...

359
00:30:37,880 --> 00:30:39,520
It’ll be fine.

360
00:30:40,280 --> 00:30:44,160
Actually, this is one thing
I absolutely won’t give up.

361
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:47,480
Why?

362
00:30:49,660 --> 00:30:54,220
Because I made a promise with him.

363
00:30:54,220 --> 00:30:56,480
I wanna fly in the sky!

364
00:30:56,480 --> 00:30:58,820
I can fly!
I’ve got a cape on...

365
00:30:58,820 --> 00:31:01,480
Well, I’m gonna be an astronaut.

366
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:03,980
And I’ll plant a flag on the moon.

367
00:31:03,980 --> 00:31:06,980
Oh, I should think of a
design for the flag.

368
00:31:06,980 --> 00:31:10,480
No way, even Tabo can’t pull that off.

369
00:31:10,480 --> 00:31:15,160
They say astronauts
can’t have cavities.

370
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:17,480
- Eh!
- Really?

371
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:21,400
You’ll be fiine.

372
00:31:21,400 --> 00:31:24,940
I know you can do it, Tabo.
You’ll make it to the moon.

373
00:31:24,940 --> 00:31:26,980
Right?

374
00:31:26,980 --> 00:31:30,180
When that time comes,
I’ll take everyone with me.

375
00:31:30,180 --> 00:31:32,980
- Eh?
- It’s a promise.

376
00:31:34,480 --> 00:31:49,480
So he said… he’ll study... and get into a
good university... then... go to space...

377
00:31:51,980 --> 00:31:56,980
How long is he gonna
keep thinking like that...?

378
00:31:56,980 --> 00:31:59,980
Huh... ow...!

379
00:32:01,980 --> 00:32:03,980
That’s...

380
00:32:05,480 --> 00:32:07,480
You too, right, King?

381
00:32:15,980 --> 00:32:18,980
What... are you doing...

382
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:24,980
Hurry up... and make up.

383
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:30,480
When I get discharged...

384
00:32:32,480 --> 00:32:37,480
I’ll work hard and open
my restaurant again…

385
00:32:38,760 --> 00:32:41,980
You two better
come have a drink...

386
00:33:00,120 --> 00:33:02,620
You’re amazing...

387
00:33:08,180 --> 00:33:09,640
What’s wrong?

388
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:12,620
- Koyama is in danger.
- Huh?

389
00:33:12,620 --> 00:33:17,240
He is announcing a new service
related to space today.

390
00:33:17,240 --> 00:33:21,740
I told him he should call it off,
but he said he’d do it anyway…

391
00:33:21,740 --> 00:33:23,240
Space...

392
00:33:23,240 --> 00:33:25,300
I’m gonna be an astronaut.

393
00:33:52,480 --> 00:33:55,620
- Hello. I’ll put on the mic.
- Okay.

394
00:33:56,880 --> 00:34:00,620
CEO, there are no changes
to the schedule.

395
00:34:07,960 --> 00:34:11,140
- Here, hold this.
- Okay, I’ll take it.

396
00:34:12,780 --> 00:34:16,120
Alright, let’s make
our dream come true.

397
00:34:44,880 --> 00:34:47,620
- Where’s the hall?
- In the back.

398
00:35:05,120 --> 00:35:09,120
Thank you all for coming today.

399
00:35:11,120 --> 00:35:12,980
How is it?

400
00:35:12,980 --> 00:35:15,360
I don’t know, but...

401
00:35:16,380 --> 00:35:21,120
Today, we will take you on a space trip.

402
00:35:33,860 --> 00:35:37,060
56 years since
humanity landed on the moon.

403
00:35:37,060 --> 00:35:40,220
Yet we still haven’t reached Mars.

404
00:35:40,220 --> 00:35:42,960
The distance is about
50 million kilometers.

405
00:35:42,960 --> 00:35:47,300
Even driving at 100 km/h,
it would take 57 years.

406
00:35:47,300 --> 00:35:51,760
No matter how fuel-efficient,
it’s not good for your wallet.

407
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:57,800
But with this app, such a long journey
takes just five seconds.

408
00:35:57,800 --> 00:36:02,620
You can even go to distant space
where humanity has yet to reach.

409
00:36:02,620 --> 00:36:08,620
Today, we'll introduce the big step
for humanity sparked by a phone.

410
00:36:29,380 --> 00:36:34,620
Getting this far was
by no means an easy journey.

411
00:36:35,760 --> 00:36:40,620
However, this has been a
dream since childhood...

412
00:36:41,720 --> 00:36:46,680
And a promise made
with my best friend.

413
00:36:49,520 --> 00:36:53,060
As time passed and we grew up,

414
00:36:53,060 --> 00:36:57,840
what once was a big dream
somehow became smaller.

415
00:36:57,840 --> 00:37:00,620
But we mustn’t forget.

416
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:19,480
The us back then is surely watching
who we are today.

417
00:37:19,480 --> 00:37:22,120
Wondering what kind of
adults we’ve become.

418
00:37:22,120 --> 00:37:26,620
And whether we've become
the adults we wanted to be.

419
00:37:27,580 --> 00:37:37,620
I want to make my younger self proud
by taking you to a world beyond imagination!

420
00:37:55,180 --> 00:37:58,720
Thank you.
Thank you very much.

421
00:38:03,500 --> 00:38:08,120
Please move slightly to your right.

422
00:38:08,120 --> 00:38:11,480
We’ll be starting the group interview shortly...

423
00:38:11,480 --> 00:38:15,620
Press members here,
please move forward a bit.

424
00:38:16,780 --> 00:38:21,620
It’ll begin soon.
Please wait for the group interview to start.

425
00:38:23,120 --> 00:38:25,460
Thank you.

426
00:38:25,460 --> 00:38:30,920
We’ll now start the group interview.
If you have any questions, please raise your hand.

427
00:38:30,920 --> 00:38:37,620
This app is high quality and will attract attention.
Any plans for versions 2 or 3?

428
00:38:37,620 --> 00:38:39,620
You’re getting ahead of yourself.

429
00:38:39,620 --> 00:38:42,120
I’d be happy if that happens, though...

430
00:38:42,120 --> 00:38:44,320
I’m confident.

431
00:38:44,320 --> 00:38:47,120
How do you feel that
your dream has come true?

432
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:48,620
I’m just happy.

433
00:38:48,620 --> 00:38:53,120
I’m interested in space myself, but
there are still many unknown areas.

434
00:38:53,120 --> 00:38:56,960
I want to see more kinds of space.
Will you take me with you?

435
00:38:56,960 --> 00:39:00,120
Definitely in the future.

436
00:39:02,220 --> 00:39:04,120
Tabo!

437
00:39:39,120 --> 00:39:40,820
Thank you.

438
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:43,960
Are you okay?

439
00:40:00,940 --> 00:40:03,940
I’m telling you,
it’s not an accident.

440
00:40:05,940 --> 00:40:09,440
I’m not the only one—
classmates have been attacked too.

441
00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:12,840
Catch the criminal already!
You’re the police, right?

442
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:17,440
Please calm down.
We’ll contact you if we find out anything.

443
00:40:29,440 --> 00:40:31,440
Mr. Koyama.

444
00:40:32,940 --> 00:40:36,940
Excuse me.
Can I have a word with you?

445
00:41:01,040 --> 00:41:03,500
Sonoko, are you okay?

446
00:41:03,500 --> 00:41:05,440
Ah... I’m okay.

447
00:41:05,440 --> 00:41:07,240
Ah, that’s good.

448
00:41:08,440 --> 00:41:10,440
I’m fine.

449
00:41:10,440 --> 00:41:11,940
That’s good.

450
00:41:17,180 --> 00:41:20,280
Since it’s an accident,
we’re not going to pursue it.

451
00:41:20,280 --> 00:41:22,360
I see...

452
00:41:28,800 --> 00:41:32,440
Are you okay?
Do you want some water or anything?

453
00:41:32,440 --> 00:41:35,940
- I’m good.
- Yeah...

454
00:41:41,340 --> 00:41:43,780
Ugh, I’m tired.

455
00:41:44,840 --> 00:41:48,140
First time being questioned
by the cops, so I was nervous.

456
00:41:48,140 --> 00:41:50,440
Felt like a drama really.

457
00:41:50,440 --> 00:41:53,440
It’s turned into a big deal.
Are you okay?

458
00:41:53,440 --> 00:41:55,040
I’m fine.

459
00:41:56,180 --> 00:41:58,440
- Nice place.
- Yeah.

460
00:41:58,440 --> 00:42:00,400
Thanks!

461
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:04,380
- Ah... I’m Takahiro Koyama.
- I’m Imakuni, the owner.

462
00:42:04,380 --> 00:42:06,800
We’re the same age,
so let’s drop the formal talk.

463
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:09,440
- Okay.
- Obelisk!

464
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:15,440
- Ah... you know it?
- Of course!

465
00:42:15,440 --> 00:42:18,940
The God Card, so nostalgic!

466
00:42:18,940 --> 00:42:20,400
God?

467
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:23,440
Obelisk, Ra, Osiris are
the God Cards...

468
00:42:23,440 --> 00:42:25,440
Huh...?

469
00:42:25,440 --> 00:42:27,440
Th... th... this...

470
00:42:29,440 --> 00:42:31,680
Is this what they call brotherhood?

471
00:42:31,680 --> 00:42:34,100
No, no, this is...

472
00:42:34,100 --> 00:42:36,720
- A duelist.
- Huh?

473
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:40,120
- I don’t get it.
- It’s a duelist.

474
00:42:40,120 --> 00:42:42,380
- Shall we drink?
- Yeah.

475
00:42:42,380 --> 00:42:44,340
You guys too, let’s drink.

476
00:42:44,340 --> 00:42:46,440
- Huh? Is that okay?
- Is it okay?

477
00:42:46,440 --> 00:42:50,340
- Thank you!
- Let’s drink…!

478
00:42:50,340 --> 00:42:52,440
Yes!

479
00:42:52,440 --> 00:42:54,440
Lucky!

480
00:42:58,140 --> 00:42:59,680
OK?

481
00:42:59,680 --> 00:43:01,440
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

482
00:43:04,940 --> 00:43:06,800
- Thanks.
- You’re welcome.

483
00:43:06,800 --> 00:43:09,940
You don’t play?
That’s too bad.

484
00:43:09,940 --> 00:43:13,940
You’re missing out
if you don’t play this.

485
00:43:20,100 --> 00:43:22,400
“Hin, Kantaro, Niko, Tabo…”

486
00:43:24,100 --> 00:43:27,440
This can’t be a coincidence.

487
00:43:27,440 --> 00:43:30,660
Yeah.

488
00:43:30,660 --> 00:43:32,940
Takeda.

489
00:43:32,940 --> 00:43:34,940
Sakurai.

490
00:43:34,940 --> 00:43:36,940
Nakajima.

491
00:43:36,940 --> 00:43:38,440
Koyama.

492
00:43:38,440 --> 00:43:41,940
There are only two left.

493
00:43:44,300 --> 00:43:47,000
If the next target is…

494
00:43:49,100 --> 00:43:51,440
One day Hin…

495
00:43:51,440 --> 00:43:53,560
In the forest Kantaro…

496
00:43:53,560 --> 00:43:55,640
A bear and Nico…

497
00:43:55,640 --> 00:43:57,700
Met Tabo…

498
00:43:57,700 --> 00:44:02,440
A forest path in bloom with Chonmage…

499
00:44:08,940 --> 00:44:10,940
Haryu.
